A woman has claimed she got very creative when it came to getting revenge on her ex who cheated on her. TikTok user @kykynicolee uploaded a video saying how she posed as a recruiter and put her love rat partner through a grueling month-long job interview – before rejecting him. New York-based Kylah claimed: “When my ex cheated on me so I posed as a LinkedIn recruiter and made him go thru a month long interview process and then sent him a rejection letter about how he’s not s***”. She added in the caption: “his resume was trash anyways.” Her clip has racked up over 1.9 million views and has certainly struck a chord online. It’s not clear if the video is a joke or serious, but many people took to the comments to share their thoughts on the extreme revenge method. One said: “u should have a series called evil.” Another added: “this is absolutely genius thank you for the idea.” A third commented: “DAMN IMPRESSED.” However, not everyone was impressed, with one saying: “I hope this is a joke because….” This story originally appeared on the Sun and was reproduced here with permission.